NCIt Definition: Problem related to the interaction between the patient and a medical device.
CDRH Definition: Problem related to the interaction between the patient and the device.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the interaction between the patient's physiology or anatomy and the device that affects the patient and/or the device.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the interaction between the patient's physiology or anatomy and the device that affects the patient and/or the device.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with undesirable local or systemic effects due to exposure to device materials or leachates from those materials by a patient who has an implant or is receiving treatment with a device made from them.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with undesirable local or systemic effects due to exposure to medical device materials or leachates from those materials by a patient who has an implant or is receiving treatment with a device made from them.

NCIt Definition: The device appears to elicit undesired response in the patient to the presence of an implanted or invasive device, without inherent device failure, e.g. fibrous encapsulation, or inflammation of the tissue around the device, or extrusion of the device.
CDRH Definition: The device appears to elicit undesired response in the patient to the presence of an implanted or invasive device, without inherent device failure, e.g. fibrous encapsulation, or inflammation of the tissue around the device, or extrusion of the device.

NCIt Preferred Term: Inadequacy of Device Shape and/or Size
NCIt Definition: The physical size and/or shape of the device was inadequate with regard to the patient's anatomy.
CDRH Preferred Term: Inadequacy of Device Shape and/or Size
CDRH Definition: The physical size and/or shape of the device was inadequate with regard to the patient's anatomy.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with interconnection between the bone tissue and the implanted device.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with interconnection between the bone tissue and the implanted device.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the failure to see direct anchorage of an implant by the formation of bony tissue around the implant without the growth of fibrous tissue at the bone-implant interface.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the failure to see direct anchorage of an implant by the formation of bony tissue around the implant without the growth of fibrous tissue at the bone-implant interface.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with weakened integration of the device at the bone-implant interface due to loss of fibrous and/or bony tissue and leading to compromised anchorage of the device. i.e. 'Loosening/Lysis.'
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with weakened integration of the device at the bone-implant interface due to loss of fibrous and/or bony tissue and leading to compromised anchorage of the device. i.e. Loosening/Lysis

NCIt Preferred Term: Loosening of Implant Not Related to Bone-Ingrowth
NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the loss of direct anchorage of an implanted device over time or due to an injury.
CDRH Preferred Term: Loosening of Implant Not Related to Bone-Ingrowth
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the loss of direct anchorage of an implanted device over time or due to an injury.

NCIt Definition: Problem with an implanted or invasive device moving within the body, or being completely expelled from the body.
CDRH Definition: Problem with an implanted or invasive device moving within the body, or being completely expelled from the body.

NCIt Definition: Problem with all or part of an implanted or invasive medical device being completely expelled from its intended location within the body.
CDRH Definition: Problem with all or part of an implanted or invasive device being completely expelled from its intended location within the body.

NCIt Definition: Problem with all or part of an implanted or invasive device moving from its intended location within the body.
CDRH Definition: Problem with all or part of an implanted or invasive device moving from its intended location within the body.

NCIt Definition: Problems associated with a product having less efficacy than expected. No other malfunctions could be identified.
CDRH Definition: Problems associated with a product having less efficacy than expected. No other malfunctions could be identified.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the narrowing or obstruction of the device (e.g. prosthetic heart valves, stents, etc.).
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the narrowing or obstruction of the device (e.g. prosthetic heart valves, stents, etc.).

NCIt Definition: Problem related to the settling or collapse of bone adjacent to an implanted device.
CDRH Definition: Problem related to the settling or collapse of bone adjacent to an implanted device, in direction of the loading force.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with any deviations from the documented specifications of the device that relate to nonconformity during manufacture to the design of an item or to specified manufacturing, packaging or shipping processes (out of box problem).
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with any deviations from the documented specifications of the device that relate to nonconformity during manufacture to the design of an item or to specified manufacturing, packaging or shipping processes (out of box problem).

NCIt Definition: A difficulty with the quality of part of the device or the device itself.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with an inherent device characteristic that is not satisfactory as specified or delivered.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with a device not being as sharp as intended or expected.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with a device not being as sharp as intended or expected.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device that does not meet the specifications or requirements for which it was manufactured (e.g. materials, parts, manufacturing process).
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the device that does not meet the specifications or requirements for which it was manufactured (e.g. materials, parts, manufacturing process).

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with a device component having flaws of dimensional deviations greater than acceptable for the intended use.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with a device component having flaws of dimensional deviations greater than acceptable for the intended use.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with having flaws or dimensional deviations greater than acceptable for the intended use of the device.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with having flaws or dimensional deviations greater than acceptable for the intended use of the device.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with packaging or shipping damage prior to the use of a device.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with packaging or shipping damage prior to the use of the device.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the materials used to construct the cover or outer wrapping of the device.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the materials used to construct the cover or outer wrapping of the device.

NCIt Preferred Term: Difficult to Open or Remove Packaging Material
NCIt Definition: Problem associated with difficulty for users to operate the device, specifically as it relates to the opening or removal of the outer wrapping.
CDRH Preferred Term: Difficult to Open or Remove Packaging Material
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with difficulty for users to operate the device, specifically as it relates to the opening or removal of the outer wrapping.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the nonconformance to the device specifications due to incomplete or missing packaging that may compromise the device operation as intended.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the nonconformance to the device specifications due to incomplete or missing packaging that may compromise the device operation as intended.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device's loss of packaging seal.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the loss of packaging seal.

NCIt Preferred Term: Tear, Rip or Hole in Packaging
NCIt Definition: Problem associated with packaging damage (tear, rip or hole) prior to the use of the device.
CDRH Preferred Term: Tear, Rip or Hole in Device Packaging
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with packaging damage (tear, rip or hole) prior to the use of the device.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with medical device packaging that looks similar to another product.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with medical device packaging that looks similar to another product leading to confusion. The other product may be another device or a different product such as a medicine or cleaning agent. Use A210107 for Device label look-alike.

NCIt Preferred Term: Device Misassembled during Manufacturing or Shipping
NCIt Definition: A device found incorrectly assembled when delivered to the user facility.
CDRH Definition: A device found incorrectly assembled when delivered to the user facility.

NCIt Definition: A device is found to have one or more components incorrectly assembled when delivered to the user facility.
CDRH Definition: A device found to have one or more components incorrectly assembled when delivered to the user facility. This includes cases in which components are interchanged.

NCIt Definition: A device component(s) found to be missing when delivered to the user facility.
CDRH Definition: A device component(s) found to be missing when delivered to the user facility.

NCIt Definition: More than the usual number of components present/additional components from this or other devices.
CDRH Definition: More than the usual number of components present/additional components from this or other devices.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with shipping damage or problem prior to the use of the device.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with shipping damage or problem prior to the use of the device.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with a device being received in such a manner to indicate that its sterility has been compromised (e.g. sterile packaging breached, visible contaminate present).
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with a device being received in such a manner to indicate that its sterility has been compromised (e.g. sterile packaging breached, visible contaminate present)

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with any from the documented specifications of a device that relate to any chemical characterization, i.e., element, compound, or mixture.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with any from the documented specifications of the device that relate to any chemical characterization, i.e., element, compound, or mixture.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with an unexpected or inappropriate smell released by the device.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with an unexpected or inappropriate smell released by the device.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with any deviations from the documented specifications of the device that relate to any ingredient or reagent characterization.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with any deviations from the documented specifications of the device that relate to any ingredient or reagent characterization.

NCIt Preferred Term: Clumping in Device or Device Ingredient
NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the aggregation of particles into irregular masses.
CDRH Preferred Term: Clumping in Device or Device Ingredient
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the aggregation of particles into irregular masses.

NCIt Preferred Term: Coagulation in Device or Device Ingredient
NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the undesired characterization of congealing, solidifying, thickening, curdling.
CDRH Preferred Term: Coagulation in Device or Device Ingredient
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the undesired characterization of congealing, solidifying, thickening, curdling.

NCIt Preferred Term: Precipitate in Device or Device Ingredient
NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the separation of solid particles from a liquid as the result of a chemical or physical change.
CDRH Preferred Term: Precipitate in Device or Device Ingredient
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the separation of solid particles from a liquid as the result of a chemical or physical change.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the degree to which an antibody or antigen participates in cross reactions.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the degree to which an antibody or antigen participates in cross reactions.

NCIt Definition: Substances that consist of separate particles that are introduced by the device during use.
CDRH Definition: Substances that consist of separate particles that are introduced by the device during use.

NCIt Definition: pH higher than expected and/or anticipated.
CDRH Definition: pH higher than expected and/or anticipated.

NCIt Definition: pH lower than expected and/or anticipated.
CDRH Definition: pH lower than expected and/or anticipated.

NCIt Definition: Color of product is different from that expected.
CDRH Definition: Color of product is different from that expected.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with an unexpected or incomplete chemical reaction or effect.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with an unexpected or incomplete chemical reaction or effect.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with any deviations from the documented specifications of the device that relate to the limited durability of all material used to construct the device.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with any deviations from the documented specifications of the device that relate to the limited durability of all material used to construct device.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with undesired damage or breakage of those materials used in the device construction.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with undesired damage or breakage of those materials used in the device construction.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with a partial or full-thickness crack in the device materials.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with a partial or full-thickness crack in the device materials.

NCIt Preferred Term: Loss of or Failure to Bond
NCIt Definition: Problem associated with lack or loss of adherence between materials intended to be joined together by bonding.
CDRH Preferred Term: Loss of or Failure to Bond
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with lack or loss of adherence between materials intended to be joined together by any bonding such as an adhesive, heat welding, etc.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with small pieces of the device breaking off unexpectedly.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with small pieces of the device breaking off unexpectedly.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with undesired damage or breakage in a solder joint of materials used in the device construction.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with undesired damage or breakage in a solder joint of materials used in the device construction.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the pressure inside a vessel or container rising to such a degree that the container ruptures.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the pressure inside a vessel or container rising to such a degree that the container ruptures.

NCIt Definition: Problem with the device associated with the violent bursting due to the sudden expansion of air, gas or fluid.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the violent bursting due to the sudden expansion of air, gas or fluid.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with an undesired partial separation and/or a visible opening along the length or width in the materials that are used in the device construction.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with an undesired partial separation and/or a visible opening along the length or width in the materials that are used in the device construction.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with a undesired change in the chemical structure, physical properties, or appearance in the materials that are used in the device construction.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with a undesired change in the chemical structure, physical properties, or appearance in the materials that are used in the device construction.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with buildup of calcium salts on a device.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with buildup of calcium salts on the device.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the chemical or electrochemical reaction between materials, usually a metal and its environment that produces a deterioration of the metal and its properties.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the chemical or electrochemical reaction between materials, usually a metal and its environment that produces a deterioration of the metal and its properties.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with a progressive loss of a material from a solid surface.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with a progressive loss of a material from a solid surface.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the corrosion of a material's surface, confined to a point or small area that takes the form of cavities.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the corrosion of a material's surface, confined to a point or small area that takes the form of cavities.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the detachment of small pieces of the coating film of a material.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the detachment of small pieces of the coating film of a material.

NCIt Definition: Peeling or delamination of composite materials, including coatings, that occurs when layers are separated as a result of stress or impact and resulting in loss of mechanical toughness.
CDRH Definition: Peeling or delamination of composite materials, including coatings, that occurs when layers are separated as a result of stress or impact and resulting in loss of mechanical toughness.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with material damage to a surface, usually involving progressive loss or displacement of material, due to relative motion between that surface and a contacting substance or substances.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with material damage to a surface, usually involving progressive loss or displacement of material, due to relative motion between that surface and a contacting substance or substances.

NCIt Definition: Problem due to the device's undesired unravelling of material (e.g. disentangled, unwound etc.).
CDRH Definition: Problem due to the undesired unravelling of material (e.g. disentangled, unwound etc.).

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with an undesired material change in shape or property caused by external forces.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with an undesired material change in shape or property caused by external forces.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with an undesired bulge, bend, bow, kink, or wavy condition observed in the device material resulting from compressive stresses.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with an undesired bulge, bend, bow, kink, or wavy condition observed in the device material resulting from compressive stresses.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with a undesired change in shape, characterized by the presence of a slight hollow (dent) in the device surface.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with a undesired change in shape, characterized by the presence of a slight hollow (dent) in the device surface.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with an undesired material change in the physical property of the device which is characterized by failure to fold.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with an undesired material change in physical property, characterized by failure to fold.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the comprising materials' deformation in that device fails to open its wrapping or open/extend in a certain manner i.e. balloon or lens.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the comprising materials' deformation in that device fails to open its wrapping or open/extend in a certain manner i.e. balloon or lens.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the comprising materials having damaged edges.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the comprising materials having damaged edges.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with an undesired material change in shape, characterized by the infolding of one part within another part of a structure.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with an undesired material change in shape, characterized by the infolding of one part within another part of a structure.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with an undesired material change in physical property, characterized by rigidity (it resists deformation in response to an applied force).
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with an undesired material change in physical property, characterized by rigidity (it resists deformation in response to an applied force).

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device material that results in the material's inability to maintain the desired shape or support function.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with any device material that results in the material's inability to maintain the desired shape or support function.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with deformations that lead to twisting or bending of the device.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with deformations that lead to twisting or bending of the device.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with a solid device being transformed into a molten or liquid state.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with a solid device being transformed into a molten or liquid state.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with an increase or elongation in a materials' dimension.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with an increase or elongation in a materials' dimension.

NCIt Definition: Device is thickened due to deformation.
CDRH Definition: Device is thickened due to deformation. Note: Not to be used for thickening of liquid.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with an undesired streak, pattern and/or a noticeable change in color from the rest of the materials used in the device construction.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with an undesired streak, pattern and/or a noticeable change in color from the rest of the materials used in the device construction.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with material breaking into small pieces.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with material breaking into small particles.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with an undesirable opaqueness or cloudiness.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with an undesirable opaqueness or cloudiness.

NCIt Definition: Material constituting device is perforated possibly compromising the device's intended purpose.
CDRH Definition: Material constituting device is perforated possibly compromising the device's intended purpose.

NCIt Definition: Device material(s) punctured leading to undesired holes/openings.
CDRH Definition: Device material(s) punctured leading to undesired holes/openings.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with undesired physical appearance of device material, specifically when material extends beyond or above device surface.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with undesired physical appearance of device material, specifically when material extends beyond or above device surface.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with perforations that lead to bursting of the device.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with perforations that lead to bursting of the device.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with an undesired disassociation or breaking apart of the device.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with an undesired disassociation or breaking apart of the device.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with materials comprising the device are split, cut or torn due to external forces (e.g. wrenching or laceration) or internal forces (e.g. exceeding the tensile stress limits belonging to the materials used in the device construction).
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with materials consisting the device are split, cut or torn due to external forces (e.g. wrenching or laceration) or internal forces (e.g. exceeding the tensile stress limits belonging to the materials used in the device construction).

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with an undesirable shallow cut or narrow groove in the surface of the device materials.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with an undesirable shallow cut or narrow groove in the surface of the device materials.

NCIt Definition: Problems associated with mechanical actions or defects of the device, which includes any moving parts or subassemblies, etc.
CDRH Definition: Problems associated with mechanical actions or defects, including moving parts or subassemblies, etc.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the separation of the device from its physical construct, integrity, or chassis.
CDRH Preferred Term: Detachment of Device or Device Component
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the separation of the device from its physical construct, integrity, or chassis.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with one device causing harm to another device.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with one device causing harm to another device.

NCIt Definition: Problems associated with the inability of or unexpected removal or separation of the device from its physical location.
CDRH Definition: Problems associated with the inability or unexpected ejection or discharge of the device from its physical location.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the inability to remove or discharge device from the location of use.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the inability of the device to be ejected or discharged from its physical location.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with unexpected discharge of the device from expected location includes but not limited to the device such as clip appliers, film cartridge, staples.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with unexpected ejection of the device from its physical location. This includes but is not limited to devices such as clip appliers, film cartridge, and staples.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the escape of a liquid or gas from the vessel or container in which it is housed.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the escape of a liquid (including blood and bodily fluids), gas or radiation from the vessel or container in which it is housed.

NCIt Definition: Escape (Release, Discharge) of fluid (including blood or bodily fluid) through an unintended location; often accompanied by a loss of pressure and/or output. This includes both external and internal fluid leak. This does not include fluidized powder leak.
CDRH Definition: Escape (Release, Discharge) of fluid (including blood or bodily fluid) through an unintended location; often accompanied by a loss of pressure and/or output. This includes both external and internal fluid leak. This does not include fluidized powder leak.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the unintended escape of a gas/air from the container in which it is housed. This also includes both external and internal air/gas leak.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the unintended escape of a gas/air from the container in which it is housed. This also includes both external and internal air/gas leak.

NCIt Definition: Escape (release, discharge) of gel through an unintended location - as in leakage of ultrasound gel. Escape or release of gel from containment structures - as in gel filled implant leak.
CDRH Definition: Escape (Release, Discharge) of gel through an unintended location - as in leakage of ultrasound gel. Escape or release of gel from containment structures - as in gel filled implant leak.

NCIt Definition: Escape of radiation (energy in the form of waves or subatomic particles, especially those that cause ionization) through containment structures, leading to unintended exposure.
CDRH Definition: Escape of radiation (energy in the form of waves or subatomic particles, especially those that cause ionization) through containment structures, leading to unintended exposure.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the escape of blood around a heart valve, particularly around its leaflets.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the escape of blood around a heart valve, particularly around its leaflets. Also known as paravalvular leak.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the escape or backward flow of blood through or across the valve.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the escape or backward flow of blood through or across the valve. Also known as transvalvular regurgitation.

NCIt Definition: Escape (release, discharge) of powder (including particulates) through an unintended location,  often accompanied by a loss of pressure and/or output.
CDRH Definition: Escape (release, discharge) of powder (including particulates) through an unintended location,  often accompanied by a loss of pressure and/or output.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with persistent blood flow/pressure in the aneurysm sac following an endovascular aneurysm repair (EVAR) procedure.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with persistent blood flow/pressure in the aneurysm sac following an endovascular aneurysm repair (EVAR) procedure.

NCIt Definition: Regurgitation of the blood of the heart valves owning to imperfect closing, insufficiency or incompetency of the valves.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the escape or backward flow of blood relative to a valve where it is not specified or not confirmed whether the leak is transvalvular/intravalvular or paravalvular/perivalvular.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device not discharging as intended.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the device not discharging as intended.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with failure of the device to discharge its load (e.g. surgical stapler failed to partially or completely deploy its staples).
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with failure of the device to discharge its load (e.g. surgical stapler failed to partially or completely deploy its staples).

NCIt Definition: Issue associated with failure of device to discharge its load (e.g., surgical stapler failed to partially or completely deploy its staples).
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with a therapy or algorithm not being delivered or executed at the expected time.

NCIt Definition: The motion of the device is prevented or restricted.
CDRH Definition: The motion of the device is prevented or restricted.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with a device mechanical functioning of machinery, moving parts or tools of device being changed or modified.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with a device mechanical functioning of machinery, moving parts or tools of device being changed or modified.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with a circuit, equipment, or system whereby its functions fail to be properly synchronized or its relative positions properly oriented.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with a circuit, equipment, or system whereby its functions fail to be properly synchronized or its relative positions properly oriented.

NCIt Definition: Inability of the device to make an incision, pierce or open as intended.
CDRH Definition: Inability of the device to make an incision, pierce or open as intended.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device failing to complete a series of processes or events.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the device failing to complete a series of processes or events.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device failing to connect tissue with a stapling device due to the staples not forming correctly.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the device failing to connect tissue with a stapling device due to the staples not forming correctly.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device failing to seal the intended vessel with the device intended to provide a seal.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the device failing to seal the intended vessel with the device intended to provide a seal (e.g. electrosurgical hemostasis).

NCIt Definition: An unintended or unpleasant sound that emanates from a device.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with any unintended sound which emanates from the device (for example, squeaking from two parts rubbing together or buzzing sounds from electrical components).

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the lack of movement in the device due parts sticking or seizing.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the lack of movement in the device due parts sticking or seizing.

NCIt Definition: Strength of an adhesive bond is too great; typically used when the adhesive is meant as a temporary hold but is acting in a more permanent manner.
CDRH Definition: Strength of an adhesive bond is too great; typically used when the adhesive is meant as a temporary hold but is acting in a more permanent manner.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with drawing back the device to an intended location.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with drawing back the device to an intended location.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the basic physical construction or physical make up of the device.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the basic physical construction or physical make up of the device.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the buckling or crushing of material from external forces.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the buckling or crushing of material from external forces.

NCIt Definition: The device has undesirable sharp edges which can cause harm or damage.
CDRH Definition: The device has undesirable sharp edges which can cause harm or damage.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the use of the device in terms of the user experiencing difficulty to close or to spread out/extend length of the device, even if the operation is being performed according to labeled instructions for use.
CDRH Preferred Term: Difficult to Fold, Unfold or Collapse
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the use of the device in terms of user experiencing difficulty to close or to spread out/extend length of the device, even if the operation is being performed according to labeled instructions for use.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the use of the device in terms of user experiencing difficulty opening and closing the device, even if the operation is being performed according to labeled instructions for use.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the use of the device in terms of user experiencing difficulty opening and closing the device, even if the operation is being performed according to labeled instructions for use.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the heart valve leaflet not closing properly.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the heart valve leaflet not closing properly.

NCIt Definition: Movement of the device to an unintended location within the body.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with an undesired movement of the device, which may be related to the device malfunction, misdiagnosis, or mistreatment.

NCIt Definition: Problems associated with the device not remaining in an expected location.
CDRH Definition: Problems associated with the device not remaining in an expected location.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the inability of the device to stay in an upright position.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the inability of the device to stay in an upright position.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device or a component unexpectedly being dropped or moving down from an intended place.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the device or a component unexpectedly being dropped or moving down from an intended place.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device moving or sliding from the intended position.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the device moving or sliding from the intended position.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device impacting with another object.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the device impacting with another object.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with any motion of the system or components that was not initiated by the user.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with any motion of the system or components that was not initiated by the user.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the mechanical stability of a device.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the mechanical stability of the device.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the undesirable mechanical oscillation in a device.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the undesirable mechanical oscillation.

NCIt Definition: Insufficient lubrication on a device.
CDRH Definition: The device shows inadequate lubrication.

NCIt Definition: Problems associated with threads that are damaged either prior to use due to bad threading or repeated re-use (possibly with other damaged components) or threads that became stripped or damaged while being used.
CDRH Definition: Problems associated with threads that are damaged either prior to use due to bad threading or repeated re-use (possibly with other damaged components) or threads that became stripped or damaged while being used.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with transmission of visible light affecting the quality of the image transmitted or otherwise affecting the intended application of the visible light path.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with transmission of visible light affecting the quality of the image transmitted or otherwise affecting the intended application of the visible light path.

NCIt Definition: The problem relates to the poor focusing of the object or the focus is on the wrong object or in the wrong area.
CDRH Definition: The problem relates to the poor focusing of the object or the focus is on the wrong object or in the wrong area.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with being off-center of optical lenses.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with being off-center of optical lenses.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with an undesired change of color.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with an undesired change of color.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with an optical defect in an image-forming system whereby the image is not the shape of an ideal image of the object.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with an optical defect in an image-forming system whereby the image is not the shape of an ideal image of the object.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the blocking of optical devices, e.g. visual pathways.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the blocking of optical devices, e.g. visual pathways.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the function of the electrical circuitry of the device.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the function of the electrical circuitry of the device.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the inability of the device to achieve successful depolarization and contraction of a cardiac chamber caused by a pacemaker output pulse.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the inability of the device to achieve successful depolarization and contraction of a cardiac chamber caused by a pacemaker output pulse.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the failure to achieve effective and consistent depolarization of the heart resulting from the electrical stimulus of the pacemaker.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the failure to achieve effective and consistent depolarization of the heart resulting from the electrical stimulus of the pacemaker.

NCIt Definition: Problem with the amount of output energy needed to cause cardiac depolarization being higher than expected/desired.
CDRH Definition: Problem with the amount of output energy needed to cause cardiac depolarization being higher than expected/desired.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the ineffective and inconsistent depolarization of the heart.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the ineffective and inconsistent depolarization of the heart.

NCIt Definition: Problem with the amount of output energy needed to cause cardiac depolarization being unstable.
CDRH Definition: Problem with the amount of output energy needed to cause cardiac depolarization being unstable.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the excessive production of electrical impulses over a period.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the excessive production of electrical impulses over a period.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with electrical current flowing through a gap between two conductive surfaces, typically resulting in a visible flash of light.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with electrical current flowing through a gap between two conductive surfaces, typically resulting in a visible flash of light.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with electrical current flowing through a gap between electrodes (conductive surfaces), typically resulting in a visible flash of light.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with electrical current flowing through a gap between electrodes (conductive surfaces), typically resulting in a visible flash of light.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with a flash of light related to an electrical discharge into a normally non conductive medium, such as air. Not associated with a discharge between two conductive surfaces.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with a flash of light related to an electrical discharge into a normally non conductive medium, such as air. Not associated with a discharge between two conductive surfaces.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the internal power of a device (e.g. battery, transformer, fuel cell or other power sources).
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the internal power of the device (e.g. battery, transformer, fuel cell or other power sources).

NCIt Definition: Problem related to increased battery internal impedance.
CDRH Definition: Problem related to increased battery internal impedance.

NCIt Definition: Problem related to decreased battery internal impedance.
CDRH Definition: Problem related to decreased battery internal impedance.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device failing to operate when not connected to a fixed power source.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the device failing to operate when not connected to a fixed power source.

NCIt Definition: Battery discharging earlier than expected.
CDRH Definition: Battery discharging earlier than expected.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the inability of a device to successfully charge an electrical source.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the inability of the device to successfully charge an electrical source.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the premature ending of the charging process (e.g. of a battery or other charge storage device).
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the premature ending of the charging process (e.g. of a battery or other charge storage device).

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with an unexpected amount of time required to charge the device (e.g. a delay in starting charging or a longer than expected charge time).
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with an unexpected amount of time required to charge the device (e.g. a delay in starting charging or a longer than expected charge time).

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with inability to initiate the appropriate charging process (e.g. of a battery or other charge storage device).
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with inability to initiate the appropriate charging process (e.g. of a battery or other charge storage device)

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the failure of a battery or other charge storage device to appropriately discharge as intended. Does not apply to defibrillation.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the failure of a battery or other charge storage device to appropriately discharge as intended. Does not apply to defibrillation.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the energy to operate the device.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the energy to operate the device.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the lack of power to run a device.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the lack of power to run the device.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with an intermittent disruption to the power to run the device.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with an intermittent disruption to the power to run the device.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the inability of the device to turn on related to energy delivered to a medical device.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the inability of the device to turn on related to energy delivered to the device.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device turning on when not intended.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the device turning on when not intended.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device feature that are designed to respond to a physical stimulus (temperature, illumination, motion, cardiac rhythms) and that do not transmit a resulting signal for interpretation or measurement.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the device feature that are designed to respond to a physical stimulus (temperature, illumination, motion, cardiac rhythms) and that do not transmit a resulting signal for interpretation or measurement.

NCIt Definition: Problem with a medical device being less sensitive to an input than intended or expected.
CDRH Definition: Problem with the device being less sensitive to an input than intended or expected.

NCIt Definition: Problem with a medical device being more sensitive to an input than intended or expected.
CDRH Definition: Problem with the device being more sensitive to an input than intended or expected.

NCIt Definition: Problem with the device not analyzing a signal.
CDRH Definition: Problem with the device not analyzing a signal.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the failure of the device to select the appropriate input signal.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the failure of the device to select the appropriate input signal.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the amount of input required by the device to detect a signal being higher than expected/desired.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the amount of input required by the device to detect a signal being higher than expected/desired.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the amount of an input required by the device to detect a signal being lower than expected/desired.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the amount of an input required by the device to detect a signal being lower than expected/desired.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the loss of the minimum amount of energy, voltage, or current needed to consistently stimulate the heart muscle.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the loss of the minimum amount of energy, voltage, or current needed to consistently stimulate the heart muscle.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the failure of the device designed to respond to a physical stimulus (as temperature, illumination, motion) to transmit a resulting signal for interpretation or measurement.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the failure of the device designed to respond to a physical stimulus (as temperature, illumination, motion) to transmit a resulting signal for interpretation or measurement.

NCIt Definition: Problem related to failure of the device to properly filter cardiac signals resulting in inappropriate device response.
CDRH Definition: Problem related to failure of the device to properly filter cardiac signals resulting in inappropriate device response.

NCIt Definition: Problem related to failure of the device to properly detect intrinsic cardiac activity and respond appropriately.
CDRH Definition: Problem related to failure of the device to properly detect intrinsic cardiac activity and respond appropriately.

NCIt Definition: Problem with the device receiving an incoming signal on an intermittent basis when expected to be continuous.
CDRH Definition: Problem with the device receiving an incoming signal on an intermittent basis when expected to be continuous.

NCIt Definition: Problem with the device inappropriately analyzing a signal.
CDRH Definition: Problem with the device inappropriately analyzing a signal.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the inability of the device to allow a current of electricity to pass or to conduct electricity continuously along an electrical path.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the inability of the device to allow a current of electricity to pass or to conduct electricity continuously along an electrical path.

NCIt Definition: Problems associated with the device's ability to respond to signals from a system designed to interrogate its status.
CDRH Definition: Problems associated with the device's ability to respond to signals from a system designed to interrogate its status.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with difficulty of a transponder system to trigger a response.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with difficulty of a transponder system to trigger a response.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device failure to appropriately respond to signals from a system designed to interrogate its status.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the device failure to appropriately respond to signals from a system designed to interrogate its status.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the inability of the device to generate a therapeutic simulated heart beat via electrical impulses.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the inability of the device to generate a therapeutic simulated heart beat via electrical impulses.

NCIt Definition: Failure of the device therapy or set of therapies to terminate the harmful cardiac rhythm that the therapy is meant to terminate.
CDRH Definition: Failure of the device therapy or set of therapies to terminate the harmful cardiac rhythm that the therapy is meant to terminate.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with an error due to imperfect timing of two operations, e.g. signal transmission time.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with an error due to imperfect timing of two operations, e.g. signal transmission time.

NCIt Definition: Failure of the device to generate a correctly-shaped pacing output, e.g., a waveform that is too wide.
CDRH Definition: Failure of the device to generate a correctly-shaped pacing output, e.g., a waveform that is too wide.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device ceasing to deliver paces.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the device ceasing to deliver paces.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with a pacing transmission process such that between any two significant instants in the same group, there is always an integral number of unit intervals. Between two significant instants located in different groups, there are not always an integral number of unit intervals.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with a pacing transmission process such that between any two significant instants in the same group, there is always an integral number of unit intervals. Between two significant instants located in different groups, there are not always an integral number of unit intervals.

NCIt Definition: Pacing voltage or pulse width is less than desired.
CDRH Definition: Pacing voltage or pulse width is less than desired.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the failure of pacing device for a limited period of time, following which the item recovers its ability to perform its required function without being subjected to any external corrective action. Note: such as failure is often recurrent.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the failure of pacing device for a limited period of time, following which the item recovers its ability to perform its required function without being subjected to any external corrective action. Note: such as failure is often recurrent.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with a pocket of skin in which the pulse generator is housed.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with a pocket of skin in which the pulse generator is housed.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the inability of the device to provide an appropriate or successful electrical shock.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the delivery of electrical shock/stimulation by a device intended to deliver shocks/stimulation.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the failure of the device to deliver electrical energy intended to change an electrical rhythm.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the failure of the device to deliver electrical energy.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the inappropriate delivery of an electrical energy.
CDRH Definition: A shock was delivered with incorrect energy level or at incorrect timing.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the failure to deliver shock for a limited period of time, following which the item recovers its ability to perform its required function without being subjected to any external corrective action. Note: such as failure is often recurrent.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the failure to deliver electrical energy for a limited period of time, following which the item recovers its ability to perform its required function without being subjected to any external corrective action. Note: such a failure is often recurrent.

NCIt Definition: The device delivers unintended electrical shock.
CDRH Definition: The device delivers unintended electrical shock. Use this term for devices that are not intended to deliver shocks/stimulation.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the inability to connect conductors of an electronic system for the purpose of controlling or impeding ground currents and voltages.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the inability to connect conductors of an electronic system for the purpose of controlling or impeding ground currents and voltages.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with electrical activity of the device that exceeded the specified threshold limit of the internal integrated circuitry.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with an electrical activity that exceeded the specified threshold limit of the internal integrated circuitry.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the discharge of electricity between two bodies previously electrically charged.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the discharge of electricity between two bodies previously electrically charged.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device not powering off when a shut down was requested.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the device not powering off when a shut down was requested.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device continuing to be in an active state after deactivation was requested.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the device continuing to be in an active state after deactivation was requested.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device unexpectedly powering down.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the device unexpectedly powering down.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the ability of a system to function in its electromagnetic environment without introducing intolerable disturbances to anything in its environment.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the ability of a system to function in its electromagnetic environment without introducing intolerable disturbances to anything in its environment.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with a measure of electromagnetic radiation from equipment.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with a measure of electromagnetic radiation from equipment.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the degradation of the reception of a wanted signal caused by RF disturbance.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the degradation of the reception of a wanted signal caused by RF disturbance.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with a failure of the internal network paths or electrical circuitry (i.e. electrical components, circuit boards, wiring).
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with a failure of the internal network paths or electrical circuitry (i.e. electrical components, circuit boards, wiring)

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the transfer of energy within an electrical network by means of the capacitance between circuit nodes. It occurs when energy is coupled from one circuit to another through an electric field.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the transfer of energy within an electrical network by means of the capacitance between circuit nodes. It occurs when energy is coupled from one circuit to another through an electric field.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with an electric current travelling along an accidental path (unintended path) in a circuit.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with an electric current travelling along an accidental path (unintended path) in a circuit.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with intermittent faults in electrical/electronic interconnections.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with intermittent faults in electrical/electronic interconnections.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with electrical impedance levels between device and patient connections.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with electrical impedance levels between device and patient connections.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with higher than intended electrical impedance levels between device and patient connections.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with higher than intended electrical impedance levels between device and patient connections.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with lower than intended electrical impedance levels between device and patient connections.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with lower than intended electrical impedance levels between device and patient connections.

NCIt Definition: A device found in back-up mode. This may be an appropriate fail-safe action (e.g. end of battery life), or be caused by device malfunction or due to operator error.
CDRH Definition: A device found in back-up mode. This may be an appropriate fail-safe action (e.g. end of battery life), or be caused by device malfunction or due to operator error.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the operation of a device, related to its accuracy, and associated with the calibration of the device.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the operation of the device, related to its accuracy, and associated with the calibration of the device.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the failure of the device to perform a self-calibration procedure or process designed to assure the accuracy and proper performance of the device.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the failure of the device to perform a self-calibration procedure or process designed to assure the accuracy and proper performance of the device.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the failure of the device which is unable to regain a standard level of accuracy when performing a calibration procedure or process designed to assure the accuracy and proper performance of the device.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the failure of the device which is unable to regain a standard level of accuracy when performing a calibration procedure or process designed to assure the accuracy and proper performance of the device.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device providing imprecise measurements when compared to a reference standard.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the device providing imprecise measurements when compared to a reference standard.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with an adjustment that surpasses a set of criteria.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with an adjustment that surpasses a set of criteria.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with an adjustment that falls below a set of criteria.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with an adjustment that falls below a set of criteria.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with any deviation from the documented specifications of the device that relate to the end result, data, or test results provided by the device.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with any deviation from the documented specifications of the device that relate to the end result, data, or test results provided by the device.

NCIt Definition: Problem with any deviation from the documented specifications of a device that relates to audible feedback.
CDRH Definition: Problem with any deviation from the documented specifications of the device that relate to audible feedback. e.g. voice prompts or beeps, but not safety related alarms which are covered under "Protective Measures Problem".

NCIt Definition: Problem with audible messages which do not guide a device user to the correct action.
CDRH Definition: Problem with audible messages which do not guide a device user to the correct action.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with audible prompts which cannot be heard clearly.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with audible prompts which cannot be heard clearly.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device ceasing to provide audible prompts.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the device ceasing to provide audible prompts.

NCIt Definition: Problem with any deviation from the documented specifications of the device that relate to visual feedback. e.g. the display of information, images on a screen, or output from the device.
CDRH Definition: Problem with any deviation from the documented specifications of the device that relate to visual feedback. e.g. the display of information, images on a screen, or output from the device.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with providing incorrect display information.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with providing incorrect display information.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with legibility of the device display, compromising for instance, the reading/interpretation of patient parameters or test results. Legibility problems can be due to color, size of font, display screen contrast or other factors.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with legibility of the display, compromising for instance  the reading/interpretation of patient parameters or test results. Legibility problems can be due to color, size of font, display screen contrast or other factors.

NCIt Definition: A device that does not consistently display the same message, result, reading, or image. e.g. the display might flicker, switch between readings or messages, or go completely blank for brief periods of time.
CDRH Definition: A device does not consistently display the same message, result, reading, or image. e.g. the display might flicker, switch between readings or messages, or go completely blank for brief periods of time.

NCIt Definition: Problem with image display leading to corrupted images or readouts/measurement indications.
CDRH Definition: Problem with image display leading to corrupted images or readouts/measurement indications.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with an incorrect image orientation on the device display.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with an incorrect image orientation on the device display.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the absence of display or image.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the absence of display or image.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device ceasing to provide visual feedback.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the device ceasing to provide visual feedback.

NCIt Definition: Inadequate quality of an image or any visual representation displayed by the device, or output from the device.
CDRH Definition: Inadequate quality of an image or any visual representation displayed by the device, or output from the device.

NCIt Definition: Problem with visual messages which continue to be displayed on/by the device after the appropriate action has been taken.
CDRH Definition: Problem with visual messages which continue to be displayed on/by the device after the appropriate action has been taken.

NCIt Definition: Problem with any deviation from the documented specifications of the device that relates to tactile feedback, e.g. device vibrational prompt.
CDRH Definition: Problem with any deviation from the documented specifications of the device that relate to tactile feedback. e.g device vibrational prompt.

NCIt Definition: Problem with tactile feedback which does not guide a device user to the correct action.
CDRH Definition: Problem with tactile feedback which does not guide a device user to the correct action.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device ceasing to provide tactile feedback.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the device ceasing to provide tactile feedback.

NCIt Definition: Problem with the device's intended output of energy.
CDRH Definition: Problem with the device's intended output of energy.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the energy output from the device not being in the expected part of the spectrum.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the energy output from the device not being in the expected part of the spectrum.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the failure of the device to deliver any energy.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the failure of the device to deliver any energy.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the energy output from the device being inconsistent over time.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the energy output from the device being inconsistent over time.

NCIt Definition: Device output is exceeding the documented specifications of the device.
CDRH Definition: Device output is exceeding the documented specifications of the device.

NCIt Definition: Device output is below the documented specifications of the device.
CDRH Definition: Device output is below the documented specifications of the device.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the failure of the device to deliver the output required for treatment or identification of a disease.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the failure of the device to deliver the output required for treatment or identification of a disease.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device causing unintended therapeutic action to an area of the body other than the intended area.
CDRH Preferred Term: Therapy Delivered to Incorrect Body Area
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the device causing unintended therapeutic action to an area of the body other than the intended area.

NCIt Definition: Problem with the device's intended output of radiation.
CDRH Definition: Problem with the device's intended output of radiation.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the absence of radiation output from radiological or diagnostic devices.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the absence of radiation output from radiological or diagnostic devices.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with excessive radiation emitted from radiological or diagnostic devices.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with excessive radiation emitted from radiological or diagnostic devices.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with too little radiation emitted from radiological or diagnostic devices.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with too little radiation emitted from radiological or diagnostic devices.

NCIt Definition: Device-emitted radiation when it was not supposed to. This applies to devices which are intended to emit radiation, and the radiation being emitted from the correct part of the device, but at an incorrect time.
CDRH Definition: Device-emitted radiation when it was not supposed to. This applies to devices which are intended to emit radiation, and the radiation being emitted from the correct part of the device, but at an incorrect time. Use "radiation leak" if the device emits radiation which should never have been emitted, or from a location from which it should never be emitted.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with gas output.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with gas output.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with no measurement outcome, value or data obtained from the device.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with no measurement outcome, value or data obtained from the device.

NCIt Preferred Term: Incorrect, Inadequate or Imprecise Result or Readings
NCIt Definition: Problem associated with a nonconforming end result, data, or test results provided by the device to its performance specifications.
CDRH Preferred Term: Incorrect, Inadequate or Imprecise Result or Readings
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with a nonconforming end result, data, or test results provided by the device to its performance specifications.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with impurities or interference in a signal (e.g. ECG artifact).
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with impurities or interference in a signal (e.g. ECG artifact).

NCIt Definition: The device does not collect or transfer the sample as intended.
CDRH Definition: The device does not collect or transfer the sample.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device incorrectly reporting that something has not been detected and may mislead the operator into not taking certain actions when action should be taken.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the device incorrectly reporting that something has not been detected and may mislead the operator/user/HCP into not taking certain actions when action should be taken.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device incorrectly reporting that something has been detected and may mislead the operator to take certain actions.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the device incorrectly reporting that something has been detected and may mislead the operator/user/HCP to take certain actions.

NCIt Definition: Measurement obtained from or provided by the device is obviously incorrect.
CDRH Definition: Measurement obtained from or provided by the device is obviously incorrect.

NCIt Definition: Device results that cannot be reliably reproduced.
CDRH Definition: Device results cannot be reliably reproduced.

NCIt Definition: Reading provided by the device is too high or higher than expected.
CDRH Definition: Reading provided by the device is too high or higher than expected.

NCIt Definition: Reading provided by the device is too low or lower than expected.
CDRH Definition: Reading provided by the device is too low or lower than expected.

NCIt Definition: Test results provided by the device are too high or higher than expected.
CDRH Definition: Test results provided by the device are too high or higher than expected.

NCIt Definition: Test results provided by the device are too low or lower than expected.
CDRH Definition: Test results provided by the device are too low or lower than expected.

NCIt Definition: The device does not provide or display a valid reading.
CDRH Definition: The device does not provide or display a valid reading.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the results of a test or measurement not appearing.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the results of a test or measurement not appearing.

NCIt Definition: Erroneous/discrepant results which combine high/low and/or positive/negative results.
CDRH Definition: Reports of erroneous/discrepant results which combine high/low and/or positive/negative results. This term is not to be selected where reports indicate consistently high or low or false positive or false negative results.

NCIt Definition: Implanted device is difficult to detect on imaging modalities, e.g. insufficient visibility.
CDRH Definition: Implanted device is difficult to detect on imaging modalities, e.g. insufficient visibility.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the use of a medical device for therapeutic purposes.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the use of the device for therapeutic purposes.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device producing unintended temperatures.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the device producing unintended temperatures.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device producing temperatures that are lower than specified.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the device producing temperatures that are lower than specified.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device which has a warming or heating function, and is producing excessive heat.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the device which have a warming or heating function, producing excessive heat.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device insufficiently cooled in device active (working) or/and non-active (nonworking) state.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the device insufficiently cooled in device active (working) or/and non-active (nonworking) state.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device or its components producing temperatures that are not as high as what is specified.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the device or its components producing temperatures that are not as high as what is specified.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device producing high temperatures, such that its operation is compromised or harm is caused (e.g. overheating that produces melting of components or automatic shutdown).
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the device producing high temperatures, such that its operation is compromised or harm is caused (e.g. overheating that produces melting of components or automatic shutdown).

NCIt Definition: Problems associated with a discoloration or destruction as a result of thermal decomposition of the device.
CDRH Definition: Problems associated with a discoloration or destruction as a result of thermal decomposition of the device.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the combustion of the device with a steady flame.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the combustion of the device with a steady flame.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the device-related burn with an unsteady flame.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with device-related burn with an unsteady flame.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with a cloud of vapor or gas generated from the device, generally associated after a fire or a burn.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with a cloud of vapor or gas generated from the device, generally associated after a fire or a burn.

NCIt Definition: Issue associated with written programs, codes, and/or software system that affects device performance or communication with another device.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with written programs, codes, and/or software system that affects device performance or communication with another device.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the deviations from documented system specifications that affects overall system performance and/or the performance of an individual medical device connected to that system.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the deviations from documented system specifications that affects overall system performance and/or the performance of an individual device connected to that system.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the requirement for software to fulfill its function within an intended use or application.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the requirement for software to fulfill its function within an intended use or application.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with freezing and/or becoming nonfunctional of an application program.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with freezing and/or becoming nonfunctional of an application program.

NCIt Preferred Term: Dose Calculation Error in Application Program
NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the written program code or application software used by a device to calculate specific measurements or quantities managed by the device.
CDRH Preferred Term: Application Program Problem: Dose Calculation Error
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the written program code or application software used by the device to calculate specific measurements or quantities managed by the device.

NCIt Preferred Term: Medication Error due to Application Program Problem
NCIt Definition: An error in medication preparation or administration attributed to software.
CDRH Definition: Event in which the device software results in errors of medication preparation or administration.

NCIt Preferred Term: Parameter Calculation Error due to Application Program Problem
NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the written program code or application software used by a device to calculate parameters other than those related to dose or power.
CDRH Preferred Term: Application Program Problem: Parameter Calculation Error
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the written program code or application software used by the device to calculate parameters other than those related to dose or power.

NCIt Preferred Term: Power Calculation Error due to Application Program Problem
NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the written program code or application software used by a device for calculations related to device power.
CDRH Preferred Term: Application Program Problem: Power Calculation Error
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the written program code or application software used by the device for calculations related to device power.

NCIt Preferred Term: Application Program Version or Upgrade Problem
NCIt Definition: Problem associated with installing updates to a software system that affects a device performance or communication with another device.
CDRH Preferred Term: Application Program Version or Upgrade Problem
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with installing updates to a software system that affects the device performance or communication with another device.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with installing a medical device software in a manner that allows full functioning of a medical device. Source of installation could be manufacturer or user.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with installing the device software in a manner that allows full functioning of the device. Source of installation could be manufacturer or user.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with an unintended shut down by malfunction of the application program.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with an unintended shut down by malfunction of the application program.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with execution problems relating to program or algorithm.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with execution problems relating to program or algorithm.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with a delayed execution relating to program or algorithm.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with delayed execution relating to program or algorithm.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with intermittent execution relating to program or algorithm.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with intermittent execution relating to program or algorithm.

NCIt Definition: Problem associated with the failure of a program or algorithm to execute. Sudden /unexpected interruption to a program's execution.
CDRH Definition: Problem associated with the failure of a program or algorithm to execute. Sudden/unexpected interruption to a program's execution.
