NCIt Definition: The device's ability to change genetic information (usually DNA) of an organism and thus increasing the frequency of mutations.
CDRH Definition: The device's ability to change genetic information (usually DNA) of an organism and thus increasing the frequency of mutations.

NCIt Definition: The device affects or impacts the blood or its components. (See ISO 10993 all parts)
CDRH Definition: The device affects or impacts the blood or its components. (See ISO 10993 all parts)

NCIt Definition: The device affects the ability of the blood to clot which may be induced by chemical, mechanical, or thermal properties of the device.
CDRH Definition: The device affects the ability of the blood to clot which may be induced by chemical, mechanical, or thermal properties of the device.

NCIt Definition: The device affects the body's ability to activate the complement system of the immune system, thereby interfering with the ability to clear pathogens. This may be caused by an interaction of the device with chemicals or materials.
CDRH Definition: The device affects the body's ability to activate the complement system of the immune system, thereby interfering with the ability to clear pathogens. This may be caused by an interaction of the device with chemicals or materials.

NCIt Definition: The device affects the body's ability to activate platelet formation.
CDRH Definition: The device affects the body's ability to activate platelet formation.

NCIt Definition: The device causes the formation of blood clots in or along blood vessels resulting in disturbed or disrupted blood flow.
CDRH Definition: The device causes the formation of blood clots in or along blood vessels resulting in disturbed or disrupted blood flow.

NCIt Definition: Unintended or unexpected presence of allergens in the device.
CDRH Definition: Unintended or unexpected presence of allergens in the device. If the presence of the allergen is expected but not adequately labelled, then use "Labelling Problem".

NCIt Definition: The device affects reproductive function, embryo development (teratogenicity), and prenatal and early postnatal development. (ISO 10993 part 3)
CDRH Definition: The device affects reproductive function, embryo development (teratogenicity), and prenatal and early postnatal development. (ISO 10993 part 3)

NCIt Definition: Undesirable presence of endogenous substances, body fluids, cellular tissues, etc.
CDRH Definition: Undesirable presence of endogenous substances, body fluids, cellular tissues, etc.

NCIt Definition: Events associated with an electrically powered device where an electrical malfunction results in a device problem (e.g. electrical circuitry, contact or component failed) even if the problem is intermittent.
CDRH Definition: Events associated with an electrically powered device where an electrical malfunction results in a device problem (e.g. electrical circuitry, contact or component failed) even if the problem is intermittent.

NCIt Definition: The performance of an electrical or electronic component was found to be inadequate.
CDRH Definition: The performance of an electrical or electronic component was found to be inadequate.

NCIt Definition: Problems that results from improper sequential activation of components.
CDRH Definition: Problems that results from improper sequential activation of components.

NCIt Definition: Problems due to insufficient or excessive resistance to current flow either by the device or circuit.
CDRH Definition: Problems due to insufficient or excessive resistance to current flow either by the device or circuit.

NCIt Definition: Problems due to inadequate or incorrect electrical insulation material.

NCIt Definition: The undesirable presence of living organisms such as bacteria, fungi, or viruses or their products (enzymes or toxins).
CDRH Definition: Problems traced to underlying framework, systems, and processes at the healthcare facility or other point of use (e.g. as building power supply, network, oxygen systems).

NCIt Definition: Problems caused by exposure to environmental conditions outside the expected range.
CDRH Definition: Problems caused by exposure to environmental conditions outside the expected range.

NCIt Definition: Problems traced to improper routine or preventative maintenance.
CDRH Definition: Problems traced to improper routine or preventative maintenance.

NCIt Definition: Problems caused by inadequate training.
CDRH Definition: Problems caused by inadequate training.

NCIt Definition: Problems that occur as the result of problems with the labeling (including package inserts, instruction manuals, instructions for use).
CDRH Definition: Problems that occur as the result of problems with the labeling (including package inserts, instruction manuals, instructions for use).

NCIt Preferred Term: Cause Traced to Non-Device Related Factors
NCIt Definition: The adverse event that occurred is not attributable to a device.
CDRH Preferred Term: Cause Traced to Non-Device Related Factors
CDRH Definition: The adverse event that occurred is confirmed to have been caused by something other than the device or usage.

NCIt Preferred Term: Adverse Event Related to Patient Condition
NCIt Definition: An existing condition or disease is demonstrably responsible for the adverse event and use of the device has neither caused nor otherwise influenced this condition/disease-related adverse event.
CDRH Preferred Term: Adverse Event Related to Patient Condition
CDRH Definition: An existing condition or disease is demonstrably responsible for the adverse event and use of the device has neither caused nor otherwise influenced this condition/disease-related adverse event.

NCIt Definition: The adverse event occurred during the procedure and the device had no influence on event.
CDRH Definition: The adverse event occurred during the procedure and the device had no influence on event.

NCIt Definition: The adverse event occurred because the material being used to calibrate or assess IVD performance did not have similar properties to those of human samples, leading to inappropriate bias and erroneous results. Examples of materials include: reference materials, calibrators, proficiency testing samples.
CDRH Definition: The adverse event occurred because the material being used to calibrate or assess IVD performance did not have similar properties to those of human samples, leading to inappropriate bias and erroneous results. Examples of materials include: reference materials, calibrators, proficiency testing samples.

NCIt Definition: The adverse event was caused partially or wholly by the user of the device including sample handling.
CDRH Definition: The adverse event caused partially or wholly by the user of the device including sample handling.

NCIt Definition: Problems traced to the user not following the manufacturer's instructions.
CDRH Definition: Problems traced to the user not following the manufacturer's instructions.

NCIt Preferred Term: Unintended Use Error Caused or Contributed to Event
NCIt Definition: The interaction between the user and device, or sample, caused or contributed to the error. This includes unintended inappropriate use of the device and incorrect sample preparation.
CDRH Preferred Term: Unintended Use Error Caused or Contributed to Event
CDRH Definition: The interaction between the user and device, or sample, caused or contributed to the error. This includes unintended inappropriate use of the device and incorrect sample preparation.

NCIt Preferred Term: Cause Traced to Intentional Off-Label, Unapproved, or Contraindicated Use
NCIt Definition: Problems traced to the intentional use of the device in an unapproved procedure, for an unapproved patient, or for which it is contraindicated, or not listed on the label.
CDRH Preferred Term: Cause Traced to Intentional Off-Label, Unapproved, or Contraindicated Use
CDRH Definition: Problems traced to the intentional use of the device in an unapproved procedure, for an unapproved patient, or for which it is contraindicated, or not listed on the label.

NCIt Definition: A device that has exceeded the period of time/date recommended by the manufacturer for storing the device without a degradation in quality.
CDRH Definition: A device that has exceeded the period of time/date recommended by the manufacturer for storing the device without a degradation in quality.

NCIt Definition: Problems traced to the device reaching the end of its useful life.
CDRH Definition: Problems traced to the device reaching the end of its useful life.

NCIt Definition: Problems traced to the use of the device more than once when it is designed for only one use.
CDRH Definition: Problems traced to the use of the device more than once when it is designed for only one use.

NCIt Definition: Problems occurred because of willful damage or reckless misuse. This term indicates that there was an apparent intent to cause damage or injury.
CDRH Definition: Problems occurred because of willful damage or reckless misuse. This term indicates that there was an apparent intent to cause damage or injury.

NCIt Definition: Problems related to the use of a device in a way not intended in the instructions for use, but which may result from readily predictable human behavior.
CDRH Definition: Problems related to the use of a device in a way not intended in the instructions for use, but which may result from readily predictable human behavior.

NCIt Definition: Reported adverse event known and documented in the labeling (including both short or long term known complications or adverse reactions).
CDRH Definition: Reported adverse event known and documented in the labeling and all reasonable mitigation steps have been taken (including both short or long term known complications or adverse reactions).

NCIt Definition: Devices that deliberately and/or fraudulently misrepresent their identity, composition or source.
CDRH Definition: Devices that deliberately and/or fraudulently misrepresent their identity, composition or source.

NCIt Definition: Problem not confirmed or confirmation of no problem.
CDRH Definition: Either it was not confirmed that there was a problem with the device, or it was confirmed that there was no problem with the device.

NCIt Definition: The investigation findings do not clearly confirm the presence or absence of the reported problem with the device.
CDRH Definition: The investigation findings do not clearly confirm the presence or absence of the reported problem with the device.

NCIt Definition: The investigation findings clearly confirm that there was no problem with the device.
CDRH Definition: The investigation findings clearly confirm that there was no problem with the device.

NCIt Definition: The investigation findings do not lead to a clear conclusion about the cause of the reported adverse event.
CDRH Definition: The investigation findings do not lead to a clear conclusion about the cause of the reported adverse event.

NCIt Preferred Term: Cause Linked to Device but Unable to Trace More Specifically
NCIt Definition: Problems traced to the device, but the investigation could not identify the actual root cause (e.g. Design, Manufacturing, Component).
CDRH Preferred Term: Cause Linked to Device but Unable to Trace More Specifically
CDRH Definition: Problems traced to the device, but the investigation could not identify the actual root cause (e.g. Design, Manufacturing, Component).

NCIt Definition: A conclusion has yet to be established as the investigation is incomplete.
CDRH Definition: A conclusion has yet to be established as the investigation is incomplete. Do not use this code if the investigation is complete.

NCIt Definition: The concluded cause is not adequately described by any other term.
CDRH Definition: The concluded cause is not adequately described by any other term. Note: This code must not be used unless there is no other feasible code. The preferred term should be documented when submitting an adverse event report. This information will be used to determine if a new term should be added to the code table.

NCIt Definition: Problems traced to an error, flaw or fault in a computer program or system that causes it to produce an incorrect or unexpected result, or to behave in unintended ways.
CDRH Definition: Problems traced to an error, flaw or fault in a computer program or system that causes it to produce an incorrect or unexpected result, or to behave in unintended ways.

NCIt Preferred Term: Cause Traced to Artificial Intelligence Training/Validation Process
NCIt Definition: Problem traced to the process or dataset(s) used for training and/or validating artificial intelligence, including machine learning algorithms.
CDRH Preferred Term: Cause Traced to Artificial Intelligence Training/Validation Process
CDRH Definition: Problem traced to the process or dataset(s) used for training and/or validating artificial intelligence, including machine learning algorithms.

NCIt Definition: Problem is traced to be caused by another device.
CDRH Definition: Problem is traced to be caused by another device.

NCIt Definition: Problems traced to device performing inadequately or inconsistently in people with certain equality characteristics (e.g. sex, racial or ethnic origin).
CDRH Definition: Problems traced to device performing inadequately or inconsistently in people with certain equality characteristics (e.g. sex, racial or ethnic origin).

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A deficit in equilibrium, which may manifest as unsteady ambulation or inability to maintain an upright position.
CDRH Definition: A feeling of falling down which can occur whether the person is standing, sitting or lying down.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Trauma to the brain.
CDRH Definition: Damage to the brain.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A congenital neural tube closure defect resulting in the protrusion of the brain through a skull opening. When the protrusion includes the meninges, the term encephalomeningocele is used.
CDRH Definition: Hernia of brain substance and meninges through a congenital or traumatic opening of the skull.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Swelling due to an excessive accumulation of fluid in the brain.
CDRH Definition: A swelling in the brain caused by the presence of excessive fluid.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Unexpected increase in cerebral blood flow after carotid endarterectomy or carotid artery stenting presenting with a clinical triad of ipsilateral headache, seizure and focal neurologic symptoms.
CDRH Definition: Unexpected increase in cerebral blood flow after carotid endarterectomy (CEA) or carotid artery stenting (CAS).

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Abnormal enlargement of the cerebral ventricles.
CDRH Definition: Abnormal enlargement of the cerebral ventricles.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: The loss of cerebrospinal fluid.
CDRH Definition: The loss of cerebrospinal fluid into the surrounding tissues or outside the body.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Pertaining to or characterized by cognition. That operation of the mind which we become aware of objects of thought or perception; it includes all aspects of perceiving, thinking, or remembering.
CDRH Definition: Changes in perception, thinking, or remembering.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A mental state characterized by a lack of clear and orderly thought and behavior.
CDRH Definition: A mental state characterized by a lack of clear and orderly thought and behavior.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Loss of intellectual abilities interfering with an individual's social and occupational functions. Causes include Alzheimer's disease, brain injuries, brain tumors, and vascular disorders.
CDRH Definition: Loss of intellectual abilities interfering with an individual's social and occupational functions.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A violent jar or shock, or the condition which results from such an injury.
CDRH Definition: Traumatic brain injury as a result of the action of a mechanical force on the head.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Sudden, involuntary skeletal muscular contractions of cerebral or brain stem origin.
CDRH Definition: Sudden, involuntary skeletal muscular contractions of cerebral or brain stem origin.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A convulsion marked by alternating contracting and relaxing of the muscles.
CDRH Definition: A convulsion marked by alternating contracting and relaxing of the muscles.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Prolonged contraction of the muscles, as the result of an epileptic discharge.
CDRH Definition: A convulsion marked by prolonged contraction of the muscles.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A brain disorder characterized by episodes of abnormally increased neuronal discharge resulting in transient episodes of sensory or motor neurological dysfunction, or psychic dysfunction. These episodes may or may not be associated with loss of consciousness or convulsions.
CDRH Definition: Epilepsy caused or apparently caused by device. Do not use when epilepsy is a pre-existing condition.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A life-threatening situation in which the brain is in a continuous state of seizure.
CDRH Definition: A life-threatening condition characterised by a single prolonged seizure or a series of seizures without intervening full recovery of consciousness.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Lower perceptual capacity in one or more senses.
CDRH Definition: Lower capacity to notice through one or more senses.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Higher perceptual capacity in one or more senses.
CDRH Definition: Higher capacity to notice through one or more senses.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A sensation of lightheadedness, unsteadiness, turning, spinning or rocking.
CDRH Definition: A sensation of lightheadedness, unsteadiness, turning, spinning or rocking.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Impairment of verbal communication skills, often resulting from brain damage.
CDRH Definition: Impairment of verbal communication skills, often resulting from brain damage.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A term referring to the inability to speak. It may result from injuries to the vocal cords or may be functional (psychogenic).
CDRH Definition: Inability to speak.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: An inflammatory process affecting the brain parenchyma. Causes include viral infections and less frequently bacterial infections, toxins, and immune-mediated processes.
CDRH Definition: An acute inflammatory process affecting the brain parenchyma.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A functional and/or structural disorder of the brain caused by diseases (e.g. liver disease, kidney disease), medications, chemicals, and injuries.
CDRH Definition: A functional and/or structural disorder of the brain that is acquired or congenital and characterised by mental and neurological symptoms.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Pain in various parts of the head, not confined to the area of distribution of any nerve.
CDRH Definition: Pain in various parts of the head, not confined to the area of distribution of any nerve.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A disorder characterized by an abnormal increase of cerebrospinal fluid in the ventricles of the brain.
CDRH Definition: A disorder characterized by an abnormal increase of cerebrospinal fluid in the ventricles of the brain.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Bleeding within the cranium.
CDRH Definition: Bleeding within the cranium.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: An inability to purposefully respond to stimuli.
CDRH Definition: A level of awareness that can be described as consistently not responsive to stimuli.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A state of profound unconsciousness associated with markedly depressed cerebral activity. Causes include central nervous system damage, intoxication, and metabolic abnormalities.
CDRH Definition: A state of profound unconsciousness associated with markedly depressed cerebral activity.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: An episode of lightheadedness and dizziness which may precede an episode of syncope.
CDRH Definition: Extremely weak; threatened with syncope.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A spontaneous loss of consciousness caused by insufficient blood supply to the brain.
CDRH Definition: A spontaneous, transient, loss of consciousness caused by insufficient blood supply to the brain.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Systematic and extensive loss of memory caused by organic or psychological factors. The loss may be temporary or permanent, and may involve old or recent memories.
CDRH Definition: Systematic and extensive loss or impairment of memory caused by organic or psychological factors. This may be temporary or permanent, and may involve old or recent memories.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A disorder characterized by acute inflammation of the meninges of the brain and/or spinal cord.
CDRH Definition: A disorder characterized by acute inflammation of the meninges of the brain and/or spinal cord.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Neurological conditions resulting in abnormal voluntary or involuntary movement, which may impact the speed, fluency, quality and ease of movement.
CDRH Definition: Neurological conditions resulting in abnormal voluntary or involuntary movement, which may impact the speed, fluency, quality and ease of movement.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Abnormality or impairment of voluntary movement.
CDRH Definition: Difficulty moving; distortion or impairment of voluntary movement, as in tic, spasm, or myoclonus.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Partial or complete loss of function of one or more muscles. It is usually caused by damage to the nervous system.
CDRH Definition: Partial or complete loss of function of one or more muscles. It is usually caused by damage to the nervous system.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Complete paralysis of the lower half of the body including both legs, often caused by damage to the spinal cord.
CDRH Definition: Paralysis of the legs and lower part of the body.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A slight or incomplete paralysis.
CDRH Definition: A slight or incomplete paralysis.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Paralysis of all four limbs.
CDRH Definition: Paralysis of all four limbs.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: The shaking movement of the whole body or just a certain part of it, often caused by problems of the neurons responsible for muscle action.
CDRH Definition: The shaking movement of the whole body or just a certain part of it, often caused by problems of the neurons responsible for muscle action.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: The occurrence of a single contraction or a series of contractions of a muscle.
CDRH Definition: The occurrence of a single contraction or a series of contractions of a muscle.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A condition that occurs while resting or lying in bed; it is characterized by an irresistible urgency to move the legs to obtain relief from a strange and uncomfortable sensation in the legs.
CDRH Definition: A condition that is characterized by an irresistible urgency to move the legs to obtain relief from a strange and uncomfortable sensation in the legs.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Partial or complete paralysis of the facial muscles of one side of a person's face. It is caused by damage to the seventh cranial nerve. It is usually temporary but it may recur.
CDRH Definition: A partial or complete loss of function of one or more of the facial muscles resulting in paralysis of the facial regions. Includes both central and peripheral facial paralysis or palsy.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Injury to nervous tissue.
CDRH Definition: Injury to nervous tissue.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Injury to the optic nerve.
CDRH Definition: Injury to optical nerve.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Injury in the central or peripheral nervous system.
CDRH Definition: Injury to the central or peripheral nervous system.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Traumatic damage of the spinal cord.
CDRH Definition: Traumatic damage of the spinal cord.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Intense painful sensation along a nerve or group of nerves. It is caused by irritation or trauma to a nerve or inflammation of a nerve.
CDRH Definition: Intense painful sensation along a nerve or group of nerves.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A disorder affecting the cranial nerves or the peripheral nervous system. It manifests with pain, tingling, numbness, and muscle weakness. It may be the result of physical injury, toxic substances, viral diseases, diabetes, renal failure, cancer, and drugs.
CDRH Definition: A disorder affecting the cranial nerves or the peripheral nervous system. It manifests with pain, tingling, numbness, and muscle weakness.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A loss of the sensation of feeling in an area of the body.
CDRH Definition: The loss of the sensation of feeling in an area of the body.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Sensory or motor loss of peripheral nerve function due to a traumatic event. (ACC)
CDRH Definition: Injury to the peripheral nervous system.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Pain or discomfort caused by exposure of the dentin layer of tooth to thermal, tactile, or other stimuli.
CDRH Definition: Pain or discomfort caused by exposure of the dentin layer of tooth to thermal, tactile, or other stimuli.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A change from the patient's baseline sleeping pattern, in the hours slept and/or an alteration/dysfunction in the stages of sleep.
CDRH Definition: A change from the patient's baseline sleeping pattern, in the hours slept and/or an alteration/dysfunction in the stages of sleep.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A term referring to disorders characterized by the disruption of normal speech. It includes stuttering, lisps, dysarthria and voice disorders.
CDRH Definition: A term referring to disorders characterized by the disruption of normal speech. It includes stuttering, lisps, dysarthria and voice disorders.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions

CDRH Definition: A chronic adhesive arachnoiditis in the spinal arachnoid, with root and spinal cord symptoms similar to those caused by pressure from a tumor.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A sudden loss of neurological function secondary to hemorrhage or ischemia in the brain parenchyma due to a vascular event.
CDRH Definition: A sudden loss of neurological function secondary to hemorrhage or ischemia in the brain parenchyma due to a vascular event.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: An acute episode of focal or global cerebral or spinal dysfunction caused by intraparenchymal, intraventricular, or subarachnoid hemorrhage.
CDRH Definition: An acute neurological deficit caused by bleeding within the brain or between the brain and the skull.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: An acute episode of focal cerebral, spinal, or retinal dysfunction caused by infarction of brain tissue.
CDRH Definition: An ischemic condition of the brain, producing a persistent focal neurological deficit in the area of distribution of the cerebral arteries.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Conditions characterized by an alteration in the ability to perceive touch.
CDRH Definition: conditions characterized by an alteration in the ability to or perception of touch.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Increased sensitivity to tactile stimulation.
CDRH Definition: Increased sensitivity to tactile stimulation.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Impairment of tactile sensitivity manifesting as partial loss of sensitivity to sensory stimuli.
CDRH Definition: Impairment of tactile sensitivity manifesting as partial loss of sensitivity to sensory stimuli.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Abnormal cutaneous sensations of tingling, numbness, pressure, cold, and warmth that an individual experiences without the presence of a stimulus. It results from functional disturbances of sensory neurons. Causes include peripheral vascular disease, peripheral neuropathy, and nerve damage.
CDRH Definition: Abnormal touch sensations, such as burning or prickling, that occur without an outside stimulus.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Conditions characterized by an alteration in the ability to perceive taste.
CDRH Definition: Conditions characterized by an alteration in taste function or perception

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions

CDRH Definition: Inability to taste.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Abnormal sense of taste.
CDRH Definition: Distortion of taste.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: An involuntary, compulsive, repetitive stereotyped movement.
CDRH Definition: An involuntary, compulsive, repetitive stereotyped movement.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A brief attack (from a few minutes to an hour) of cerebral dysfunction of vascular origin, with no persistent neurological deficit.
CDRH Definition: A brief attack (from a few minutes to an hour) of cerebral dysfunction of vascular origin, with no persistent neurological deficit.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Unintended reaction in nervous system caused by electrical stimulation.
CDRH Definition: Unintended reaction in nerve system caused by electrical stimulation.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A non-neoplastic or neoplastic disorder that affects the brain, spinal cord, or peripheral nerves.
CDRH Definition: The report describes a non-specific problem with the nervous system. Note: Please use "Appropriate Term / Code Not Available" if the report describes a specific injury but the relevant term does not exist.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions

CDRH Definition: Pressure within the craniospinal compartment is increased.

CDRH Definition: The presence of air or gas within the cranial cavity.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A level of awareness and arousal other than normal.
CDRH Definition: A level of awareness and arousal other than normal.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A neurological state characterized by increased ability to perceive and respond.
CDRH Definition: A neurological state characterised by increased ability to perceive and respond.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A neurologic state characterized by decreased ability to perceive and respond.
CDRH Definition: A neurological state characterised by decreased ability to perceive and respond.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Injury to the dura mater, with or without damage to any other layer of the meninges.
CDRH Definition: Injury to the dura mater, with or without damage to any other layer of the meninges.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Excessive clenching of the jaw and grinding of the teeth.
CDRH Definition: Excessive clenching of the jaw and grinding of the teeth.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Change from the affected person's usual emotional state.
CDRH Definition: Change from the affected person's usual emotional state.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Apprehension of danger and dread accompanied by restlessness, tension, tachycardia, and dyspnea unattached to a clearly identifiable stimulus.
CDRH Definition: Apprehension or uneasiness which may be accompanied by restlessness, tension, tachycardia, and dyspnea.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A state of physiological or psychological stress that cannot be compensated for by normal adaptive measures.
CDRH Definition: A state of physiological or psychological stress that cannot be compensated for by normal adaptive measures.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A feeling of general discomfort or uneasiness, an out-of-sorts feeling.
CDRH Definition: A feeling of general discomfort or uneasiness, an out-of-sorts feeling.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Excited response to stimuli.
CDRH Definition: A feeling of agitation. Tending to become frustrated or upset easily.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A false sensory perception in the absence of an external stimulus, as distinct from an illusion which is a misperception of an external stimulus.
CDRH Definition: A false sensory perception in the absence of an external stimulus.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Characterized by a lack of vitality or energy.
CDRH Definition: Characterized by a lack of vitality or energy.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Thoughts of taking one's own life.
CDRH Definition: Thoughts of taking one's own life.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Preferred Term: Unspecified Mental, Emotional or Behavioral Problem
NCIt Definition: An unspecified mental, emotional or behavioral problem.
CDRH Preferred Term: Unspecified Mental, Emotional or Behavioural Problem
CDRH Definition: The report describes a non-specific Mental, Emotional or Behavioural problem. Note: Please use "Appropriate Term / Code Not Available" if the report describes a specific problem but the relevant term does not exist.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A usually reversible condition characterized by the acute and sudden development of confusion, illusions, movement changes, inattentiveness, agitation, and hallucinations. Causes include drug abuse, poisoning, infectious processes, and fluid and electrolyte imbalance.
CDRH Definition: A usually reversible condition characterized by the acute and sudden development of confusion, illusions, movement changes, inattentiveness, agitation and hallucinations.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A mental disorder characterized by personality change, impaired functioning, and loss of touch with reality.
CDRH Definition: A mental disorder characterized by personality change, impaired functioning and loss of touch with reality.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: To have difficulties staying awake or being difficult to arouse.
