CDRH Definition: A laboratory test result indicating an increase in the lactate dehydrogenase concentration of a biological sample.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A laboratory test result that indicates the presence of bacteria in the blood.
CDRH Definition: Condition that relates to the presence of viable bacteria in the bloodstream, whether associated with active disease or not.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: High blood or serum levels of ions which are attributed to one or more medical devices used, such as but not limited to Co, Cr, Ti, Ni, Mo.
CDRH Definition: High blood or serum levels of ions which are attributed to one or more medical devices used, such as but not limited to Co, Cr, Ti, Ni, Mo.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: An xray finding that indicates a void or area of tissue that is less dense. Radiolucent lines can be prognostic factors after surgical joint replacements.
CDRH Definition: Radiolucencies observed on x-ray.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: An alteration in body temperature outside the normal range.
CDRH Definition: A Change or alteration of Body Temperature to a temperature outside the range of normal body temperature.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Elevation of body temperature above normal due to inflammatory or immune responses.
CDRH Definition: Elevation of body temperature above normal due to the bodies own responses.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A condition characterized by an abnormally high body temperature. In a hyperthermic state, the hypothalamic set-point is normal but body temperature increases and overrides the ability to lose heat, resulting from exogenous heat exposure or endogenous heat production.
CDRH Definition: An abnormally high body temperature. Not fever.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Abnormally low body temperature.
CDRH Definition: Abnormally low body temperature.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Any persistent problem with walking, gait or maintaining posture (sitting, standing).
CDRH Definition: Any persistent problem with walking, gait or maintaining posture (sitting, standing).

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: The tightening of scar tissue that forms around the implant.
CDRH Definition: The tightening of scar tissue that forms around the implant.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Shivering or moderate tremors of the body often accompanied by a cold sensation.
CDRH Definition: Shivering or moderate tremors of the body often accompanied by a cold sensation.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A bluish or purplish discoloration of the skin and mucous membranes resulting from a reduced concentration of oxygenated hemoglobin in the blood.
CDRH Definition: A bluish or purplish discoloration of the skin and mucous membranes resulting from a reduced amount of oxygenated hemoglobin in the blood.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Loss of appetite.
CDRH Definition: Lack of desire for food.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A question about whether an individual has or had increased appetite.
CDRH Definition: Intense desire for food.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Permanent deformation of appearance.
CDRH Definition: An alteration of appearance, shape, size or alignment.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Accumulation of extraneous inorganic matter in tissues or cavities.
CDRH Definition: Accumulation of extraneous inorganic matter in tissues or cavities.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Deposition of calcium in the tissues. It may be the result of a metabolic disorder or long-standing infection, or it may be associated with the presence of cancer.
CDRH Definition: Deposition of calcium salt in the tissues.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Pertaining to, characterized by, or promoting sweating, e.g. procedure or an agent that promotes sweating.
CDRH Definition: Profuse sweating.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A feeling of mental or physical uneasiness, pain, or distress.
CDRH Definition: A feeling of mental or physical uneasiness, pain, or distress.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Overall tiredness and lack of energy.
CDRH Definition: A state of generalized weakness with a pronounced inability to summon sufficient energy to accomplish daily activities.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Extreme fatigue; inability to respond to stimuli.
CDRH Definition: Extreme fatigue; the inability to respond to stimuli.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: The formation of fibrous tissue.
CDRH Definition: The formation of fibrous tissue.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Abnormal epithelial-lined communication between two anatomical structures.
CDRH Definition: Abnormal epithelial-lined communication between two anatomical structures.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: The pouring forth of a fluid.
CDRH Definition: Flow or leakage of fluid other than blood, from an orifice, wound or tissue.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Pus-containing fluid that is draining from an orifice or wound.
CDRH Definition: A flow or draining of pus or exudate from an oriface or wound.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A granulomatous inflammatory reaction evoked by the presence of an exogenous material in the tissues, a characteristic feature of which is the formation of foreign body giant cells.
CDRH Definition: An inflammatory reaction evoked by the presence of an exogenous material in the tissues.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: An inflammatory reaction usually caused by infectious organisms, foreign bodies, or cholesterol deposits. It is characterized by the presence of epithelioid histiocytes and chronic inflammation.
CDRH Definition: An inflammatory reaction usually caused by infectious organisms, foreign bodies, or cholesterol deposits. It is characterized by the presence of epithelioid histiocytes and chronic inflammation.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Hair loss usually from the scalp. It may result in bald spots or spread to the entire scalp or the entire epidermis. It may be androgenetic or caused by chemotherapeutic agents, compulsive hair pulling, autoimmune disorders or congenital conditions.
CDRH Definition: Loss of hair usually from the scalp that may result in bald spots or spread to the entire scalp or epidermis.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: The protrusion of part of an organ or fibroadipose tissue through an abnormal opening.
CDRH Definition: The protrusion of part of an organ or fibroadipose tissue through an opening or weakened area.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Blood pressure that is abnormally high.
CDRH Definition: Blood pressure that is abnormally high.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Blood pressure that is abnormally low.
CDRH Definition: Blood pressure that is abnormally low.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: The presence of an increased amount of blood in a part or organ; engorgement.
CDRH Definition: The presence of an increased amount of blood in a part or organ; engorgement or bloodshot.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: An abnormal increase in the number of cells in an organ or a tissue with consequent enlargement.
CDRH Definition: An abnormal increase in the number of cells in an organ or a tissue with consequent enlargement.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Involuntary passage of stool or urine from the body.
CDRH Definition: Involuntary passage of feces and/or urine from the body.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Involuntary passage of stool from the rectum.
CDRH Definition: Inability to control voluntary passage of feces from the body.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Involuntary passage of urine outside the body.
CDRH Definition: Inability to control voluntary passage of urine from the body.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: The process of the diffusion or accumulation in a tissue or cells of a substance not normal to it or in amounts above normal. (NCI)
CDRH Definition: Permeation of foreign substances into tissues or cells.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A finding of a localized protective response resulting from injury or destruction of tissues. Inflammation serves to destroy, dilute, or wall off both the injurious agent and the injured tissue. In the acute phase, inflammation is characterized by the signs of pain, heat, redness, swelling, and loss of function. Histologically, inflammation involves a complex series of events, including dilatation of arterioles, capillaries, and venules, with increased permeability and blood flow; exudation of fluids, including plasma proteins; and leukocyte migration into the site of inflammation.
CDRH Definition: A localized physical condition in which part of the body becomes reddened, swollen, or hot and often painful.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A cell death process that is morphologically characterized by a gain in cell volume (oncosis), swelling of organelles, plasma membrane rupture and subsequent loss of intracellular contents.
CDRH Definition: The pathologic death of cells or of a portion of tissue or organ resulting from irreversible damage.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Blockage of the normal flow of the contents of an anatomical passageway.
CDRH Definition: Blockage or closing of the normal flow of the contents of an anatomical passageway.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A splitting open of an anatomical structure, zone, or organ with the exposure or discharge of its content.
CDRH Definition: A splitting open or rupture of an internal organ with the exposure or discharge of its content.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: The sensation of discomfort, distress, or agony, resulting from the stimulation of specialized nerve endings.
CDRH Definition: An unpleasant sensory and emotional experience that is associated with actual or potential tissue damage or described in such terms.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Pain in the chest.
CDRH Definition: Pain in the chest.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: An unusual or extreme paleness, state of decreased skin or mucosal coloration.
CDRH Definition: Unhealthy, pale or white appearance of the face.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Lack or absence of balanced proportions between parts or organs of the body.
CDRH Definition: Lack or absence of balanced proportions between parts or organs of the body.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A condition in which an organ or body tissue drops or bulges out of place.
CDRH Definition: A condition in which an organ or body tissue drops or bulges out of place.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: The drooping of the upper eyelid.
CDRH Definition: The drooping or downward displacement of a body part.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Preferred Term: Reaction to Medicinal Component of Device
NCIt Definition: Any local or systemic adverse reaction to the medicinal component of a combination product.
CDRH Preferred Term: Reaction to Medicinal Component of Device
CDRH Definition: Any local or systemic adverse reaction to the medicinal component of a combination product.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A life-threatening condition that requires immediate medical intervention. It is characterized by reduced blood flow that may result in damage of multiple organs. Types of shock include cardiogenic, hemorrhagic, septic, anaphylactic, and traumatic shock.
CDRH Definition: A life-threatening condition that requires immediate medical intervention. It is characterized by reduced blood flow that may result in damage of multiple organs.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Shock resulting from primary failure of the heart in its pumping function, as in myocardial infarction, severe cardiomyopathy, or mechanical obstruction or compression of the heart.
CDRH Definition: Shock resulting from primary failure of the heart in its pumping function, as in myocardial infarction, severe cardiomyopathy, or mechanical obstruction or compression of the heart.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A hypoglycemic reaction to overdosage of insulin, a skipped meal, or strenuous exercise in an insulin-dependent diabetic.
CDRH Definition: A hypoglycemic reaction to overdosage of insulin, a skipped meal, or strenuous exercise in an insulin-dependent diabetic.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Shock resulting from insufficient blood volume for the maintenance of adequate cardiac output, blood pressure and tissue perfusion.
CDRH Definition: Shock resulting from insufficient blood volume for the maintenance of adequate cardiac output, blood pressure and tissue perfusion.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Shock resulting from neurogenic vasodilation, which can be produced by cerebral trauma or hemorrhage, spinal cord injury, deep general or spinal anesthesia, or toxic central nervous system depression.
CDRH Definition: Shock resulting from neurogenic vasodilation, which can be produced by cerebral trauma or hemorrhage, spinal cord injury, deep general or spinal anesthesia, or toxic central nervous system depression.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A state of acute circulatory failure characterized by persistent arterial hypotension despite adequate fluid resuscitation or by tissue hypoperfusion unexplained by other causes.
CDRH Definition: A state of acute circulatory failure resulting from organ injury or damage in response to infection that results in dangerously low blood pressure.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Narrowing or stricture of a vessel, duct or canal.
CDRH Definition: Narrowing or stricture of a vessel, duct or canal.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: The reoccurrence of stenosis after it has been treated.
CDRH Definition: The reoccurrence of stenosis after it has been treated.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Accumulation of an excessive amount of fluid in cells or intercellular tissues.
CDRH Definition: Enlargement or expansion in size of a body part from injury or inflammation.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Swelling due to an excessive accumulation of fluid in the upper or lower extremities.
CDRH Definition: accumulation of fluid in tissues perfused by the peripheral vascular system.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Abnormally increased amount of fluid in a joint cavity, usually as a result of joint inflammation.
CDRH Definition: An abnormal collection of fluid in hollow spaces or between tissues of the joints.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A circumscribed inflammatory and often suppurating lesion on the skin or an internal mucous surface resulting in necrosis of tissue.
CDRH Definition: An open sore on an external or internal surface of the body caused by a break in the skin or mucous membrane that fails to heal.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Splitting of the sutured margins of a surgical wound. Risk factors include diabetes mellitus, obesity, and advanced age.
CDRH Definition: A complication in which the wound splits or separates after being surgically closed.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: The presence of two distinct capsular layers around an implant with an intercapsular space of the breast.
CDRH Definition: The presence of two distinct capsular layers around an implant with an intercapsular space

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Complete impairment of two or more organs or organ systems.
CDRH Definition: Complete impairment of two or more organs or organ systems. Also known as multiple organ failure.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A state of hypoperfusion that does not support normal organ perfusion or function. It can include periods of reduced, unstable, or abnormal blood pressure with near syncope, or episodes of syncope.
CDRH Definition: Abnormal or unstable blood pressure

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Change in the sound and/or speed of the voice. Causes include laryngeal polyp, laryngitis, laryngeal carcinoma, throat carcinoma, Parkinson's disease, multiple sclerosis, stroke, hypothyroidism, oral surgery, tracheostomy, tracheal injury, and laryngeal injury.
CDRH Definition: Changes in the pitch or quality of the voice, which may sound weak, scratchy, raspy, or otherwise out of the ordinary.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A set of symptoms brought on by exposure to heat that can include confusion, hot dry skin, seizures, elevated body temperature, altered mental status.
CDRH Definition: A set of symptoms brought on by exposure to heat that can include confusion, hot dry skin, seizures, elevated body temperature, altered mental status, etc. Includes heat stroke and heat exhaustion.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Abnormal enlargement of a body part or organ.
CDRH Definition: An increase in organ size via increase in cell size rather than cell number

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A breath odor that is not normal for the individual.
CDRH Definition: Unusual breath odor (e.g., halitosis, fruity/sweet breath)

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Any deviation from the normal quantity, consistency, and/or color of mucus produced by the mucous membranes.
CDRH Definition: Any deviation from the normal quantity, consistency, and/or color of mucus produced by the mucous membranes.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: A substance-specific organic brain syndrome that follows the discontinuation of administration or use, or reduction in intake of an addictive substance, e.g. opioids, barbiturates and alcohol; amphetamines or similarly acting sympathomimetics; cocaine; nicotine; sedatives, hypnotics, or anxiolytics. Syndrome manifests with diverse, often painful physical and psychological symptoms, which include but not limited to intense drug craving, anxiety, depression, insomnia, nausea, perspiration, body aches, tremors, hallucinations, and convulsions.
CDRH Definition: The substance-specific organic brain syndrome that follows the discontinuation of, or reduction in, administration or intake of an addictive substance.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Irritation of body tissue(s), other than skin.
CDRH Definition: Irritation of body tissue(s), other than skin. For skin irritation use E1720 - Skin Inflammation/Irritation

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Any weakening or degeneration, especially through lack of use.
CDRH Definition: Decrease in size of a body part, cell, organ, or other tissue. For muscular atrophy use E1621 - Muscle Weakness/Atrophy

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Not enough information available to classify the clinical signs, symptoms and conditions.
CDRH Definition: It is not clear whether any health effects occurred, or health effect appears to have occurred but there is not yet enough information available to classify the clinical signs, symptoms and conditions.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Preferred Term: Appropriate Clinical Signs, Symptoms, Conditions Term/Code Not Available
NCIt Definition: The clinical signs, symptoms and conditions are not adequately described by any other term.
CDRH Definition: The clinical signs, symptoms and conditions are not adequately described by any other term. Note: this code must not be used unless there is no other feasible code. The preferred term should be documented when submitting an adverse event report. This information will be used to determine if a new term should be added to the code table.

CDRH Subset Name: Health Effects - Clinical Signs and Symptoms or Conditions
NCIt Definition: Absence of detectable signs or symptoms.
CDRH Preferred Term: No Clinical Signs, Symptoms or Conditions
CDRH Definition: No patient involvement or, no observable clinical symptoms or a change in symptoms is identified in the patient.

NCIt Definition: Change in response to treatment or cure of a disease.
CDRH Definition: Change in response to treatment or cure of a disorder or disease.

NCIt Definition: A reduction in the desirable and beneficial effects resulting from a medical  treatment.
CDRH Definition: A reduction in the desirable and beneficial effects resulting from a medical treatment.

NCIt Definition: An increase in the desirable and beneficial effects resulting from a medical  treatment.
CDRH Definition: An increase in the desirable and beneficial effects resulting from a medical treatment.

NCIt Definition: Unanticipated desirable and beneficial effects resulting from a medical  treatment.
CDRH Definition: Unanticipated desirable and beneficial effects resulting from a medical treatment.

NCIt Definition: The cessation of life.
CDRH Definition: The cessation of life.

NCIt Definition: Death of a fetus after 10 weeks gestation.
CDRH Definition: Death in utero; failure of the product of conception to show evidence of respiration, heart beat, or definite movement of a voluntary muscle after expulsion from the uterus, with no possibility of resuscitation.

NCIt Definition: Irreversible absence of cortical and brain stem functioning.
CDRH Definition: The cessation of life due to permanent loss of brain function and brainstem for absence of responsiveness to external stimuli, absence of reflex and apnea.

NCIt Preferred Term: Delay to Diagnosis due to Device
NCIt Definition: Patient diagnosis was clinically significant delayed as a consequence of device performance.
CDRH Definition: Patient diagnosis was clinically significant delayed as a consequence of device performance.

NCIt Preferred Term: Delay to Treatment due to Device
NCIt Definition: Patient treatment was delayed as a consequence of device performance.
CDRH Definition: Patient treatment was delayed as a consequence of device performance.

NCIt Preferred Term: Disruption of Subsequent Medical Procedure due to Device
NCIt Definition: Situation in which the use of the device impedes or affects a subsequent medical procedure or use of a medicine or device.
CDRH Definition: Situation in which the use of the device impedes or affects a subsequent medical procedure or use of a medicine or device. The time elapsed between the use of the device and the medical procedure is not a factor. It is not necessary for the device to have broken or malfunctioned.

NCIt Preferred Term: Exacerbation of Existing Condition due to Device
NCIt Definition: Use of the device has lead to worsening of the existing disease or condition.
CDRH Definition: Use of the device has lead to worsening of the existing disease or condition.

NCIt Preferred Term: Hospitalization or Prolonged Hospitalization due to Device
NCIt Definition: Hospitalization or prolonged hospitalization due to the health damage accompanying the use of device.
CDRH Definition: Hospitalization or prolonged hospitalization due to the health damage accompanying the use of device.

NCIt Definition: Patient requires admission to or extension of stay in an intensive care unit.
CDRH Definition: Patient requires admission to or extension of stay in an intensive care unit.

NCIt Definition: Fetal distress, congenital physical or mental impairment or birth defect, excluding fetal death.
CDRH Definition: Fetal distress, congenital physical or mental impairment or birth defect, excluding fetal death.

NCIt Preferred Term: Inadequate/Inappropriate Treatment or Diagnostic Exposure due to Device
NCIt Definition: Patient did not receive intended treatment from a device or received inadequate treatment as a consequence of device performance.
CDRH Definition: Patient did not receive intended treatment from a device or received inadequate treatment as a consequence of device performance. This includes inadequate/inappropriate radiation dosage during procedures.

NCIt Preferred Term: No Treatment due to Device Malfunction
NCIt Definition: Patient treatment was absent as a consequence of device performance.
CDRH Definition: Patient treatment was absent as a consequence of device performance.

NCIt Definition: Receiving incorrect or incompatible whole blood or a blood component.
CDRH Definition: Receiving incorrect or incompatible whole blood or a blood component.

NCIt Definition: A dose of medicine that was not taken at the prescribed dosing interval.
CDRH Definition: A dose of medicine was not taken or delivered at the prescribed dosing interval.

NCIt Definition: An inadequate amount of a treatment.
CDRH Definition: Exposure to, or intake of, an insufficient amount of a substance.

NCIt Definition: An inadequate amount of a radiation treatment.
CDRH Definition: A lower than intended dose of radiation to a single field.

NCIt Definition: Exposure to, or intake of, an excessive amount of a substance.
CDRH Definition: Exposure to, or intake of, an excessive amount of a substance.

NCIt Definition: A higher than intended cumulative dose of radiation to a single field.
CDRH Definition: A higher than intended cumulative dose of radiation to a single field.

NCIt Definition: The worsening of a disease over time due to inadequate treatment.
CDRH Definition: The worsening of a disease over time due to inadequate treatment.

NCIt Preferred Term: Exposure to Contaminated Device/Risk of Infection
NCIt Definition: Exposure to a non-sterile device or conditions where infection is likely.
CDRH Preferred Term: Exposure to Contaminated Device/Risk of Infection
CDRH Definition: Exposure to a non-sterile device or conditions where infection is likely.

NCIt Definition: Unintended exposure to a substance.
CDRH Definition: Unintended exposure of the patient and/or healthcare providers to drugs or other substances. This can include any exposure routes such as skin, mucous membranes, and respiratory.

NCIt Definition: A mild injury, illness or impairment which can be treated with minimal or no intervention.
CDRH Definition: A mild injury, illness or impairment which can be treated with minimal or no intervention, including monitoring only.

NCIt Definition: A severe injury, illness or impairment which requires hospitalization or medical intervention.
CDRH Definition: A severe injury, illness or impairment which requires hospitalization or medical intervention.

NCIt Definition: A disease condition that persists over a significant span of time.
CDRH Definition: Disease that persists over a long period of time, cannot be prevented by vaccines or cured by medication, nor do they just disappear.

NCIt Definition: Any physical or mental impairment that interferes with an individual's ability to perform desired activities.
CDRH Definition: Any physical or mental impairment that interferes with an individual's ability to perform desired activities.

NCIt Definition: Patient suffered an illness or injury which if not treated would be fatal.
CDRH Definition: Patient suffered an illness or injury which if not treated would be fatal.

NCIt Definition: Irreversible deterioration of the state of health.
CDRH Definition: Irreversible deterioration of the state of health.

NCIt Definition: Reversible deterioration of the state of health.
CDRH Definition: Reversible deterioration of the state of health.

NCIt Definition: An incorrect diagnosis or classification of an illness or other problem.
CDRH Definition: An incorrect diagnosis or classification of an illness or other problem.

NCIt Definition: Clinically significant extended treatment time or procedural time.
CDRH Definition: Clinically significant extended treatment time or procedural time. Not to be used for prolonged hospitalization or prolonged surgery.

NCIt Definition: Patient experiencing a complication that is well documented in association with the device or procedure.
CDRH Definition: Patient experiencing a complication that is well documented in association with the device or procedure.

NCIt Definition: Decrease in lifetime/ lifespan of an individual. Decline in the normal duration or in average life.
CDRH Definition: Decrease in lifetime/ lifespan of an individual. Decline in the normal duration or in average life.

NCIt Definition: The process of allaying nervous excitement or the state of being calmed. (Taber's)
CDRH Definition: Patient required sedation or additional sedation.

NCIt Definition: Restoration of the ability to function in a normal or near normal manner following disease, illness, or injury.
CDRH Definition: Patient requires treatment to facilitate the process of recovery from injury, illness, or disease.

NCIt Definition: A diagnostic or treatment procedure performed by manual and/or instrumental means, often involving an incision and the removal or replacement of a diseased organ or tissue; of or relating to or involving or used in surgery or requiring or amenable to treatment by surgery.
CDRH Definition: One or more surgical procedures, including percutaneous or minimally invasive procedures, were required, or an existing procedure changed.

NCIt Definition: Any surgical procedure performed subsequent to a primary or initial surgical procedure.
CDRH Definition: Surgical intervention that was not planned and needed to be performed in addition to other interventions including surgical ones.

NCIt Definition: The surgical removal of all or part of a limb or other appendage.
CDRH Definition: Patient required surgical removal of limb, extremities or other external body parts.

NCIt Definition: A finding referring to a medical device that has been removed from the body, usually during a surgical procedure.
CDRH Definition: Patient required a corrective invasive procedure to remove a device, or parts/fragments of a device.

NCIt Definition: Patient required a corrective invasive procedure in which a device was repositioned.
CDRH Definition: Patient required a corrective invasive procedure in which a device was repositioned. This includes implantable, surgically invasive (penetration through the surface of the body) or invasive (penetration though a natural body orifice or permanent artificial opening, e.g. stoma) devices.

NCIt Definition: Patient required a corrective invasive procedure in which a device was replaced/revised.
CDRH Definition: Patient required a corrective invasive procedure in which a device was replaced/revised. This includes implantable, surgically invasive (penetration through the surface of the body) or invasive (penetration though a natural body orifice or permanent artificial opening, e.g. stoma) devices.

NCIt Definition: A change of surgical procedure from the original plan.
CDRH Definition: A change of surgical procedures from the original plan.

NCIt Definition: Surgery that is more complicated, more comprehensive or more extensive than planned.
CDRH Definition: Surgery that is more complicated, more comprehensive or more extensive than planned (e.g. percutaneous to open surgery).

NCIt Definition: Surgery that is lengthy or that takes longer than anticipated.
CDRH Definition: Surgery that takes longer than anticipated.

NCIt Definition: Surgical procedure unable to be completed when originally scheduled and put off until some time in the future.
CDRH Definition: Surgical procedure unable to be completed when originally scheduled and put off until some time in the future.

NCIt Definition: Termination of a surgical intervention.
CDRH Definition: Surgical procedure aborted, or unable to be completed. This applies to cases where there is no information whether the procedure will be carried out at a later time, or where it is known that surgery will not go ahead. If it is known that the procedure has been, or will be, carried out later then use F1909 - Surgical Procedure Delayed

NCIt Definition: Any event type, which results in imminent risk of death, serious injury, or serious illness to more than one individual, that requires prompt remedial action.
CDRH Definition: Any event type, which results in imminent risk of death, serious injury, or serious illness to more than one individual, that requires prompt remedial action.

NCIt Definition: Unexpected clinical deterioration of patient.
CDRH Definition: Unexpected clinical deterioration of patient.

NCIt Definition: A necessary but unplanned diagnostic intervention.
CDRH Definition: Diagnostic intervention needed to be completed that was not originally planned.

NCIt Definition: The removal of tissue specimens or fluid from the living body for microscopic examination, performed to establish a diagnosis.
CDRH Definition: Patient required removal of tissue or fluid specimen to establish a diagnosis.
Patient required additional or unexpected endoscopic procedure.

NCIt Definition: A necessary but unplanned imaging procedure.
CDRH Definition: Requirement for imaging that was not originally planned.

NCIt Definition: Patient required additional or unexpected in vitro diagnostic (IVD) testing.
CDRH Definition: Patient required additional or unexpected IVD testing.

NCIt Definition: Patient required an unforeseen medical intervention.
CDRH Definition: Patient required an unforeseen medical intervention, excluding surgery, which was not on the original treatment plan.

NCIt Definition: Use of an additional or alternative device required to achieve optimal outcome.
CDRH Definition: Use of an additional or alternative device require to achieve optimal outcome.

NCIt Definition: The injection of whole blood or a blood component directly into the bloodstream.
CDRH Definition: Patient required an infusion of whole blood or a blood component directly into the bloodstream.

NCIt Definition: Patient required additional medication or additional dose of existing medication.
CDRH Definition: Patient required additional medication or additional dose of existing medication.

NCIt Definition: Any intervention to prevent disease or infection.
CDRH Definition: A medication or course of action used to prevent a possible disease or condition from occurring.

NCIt Definition: Treatment of a disease by means of exposure of the target or the whole body to radiation. Radiation therapy is often used as part of curative therapy and occasionally as a component of palliative treatment for cancer. Other uses include total body irradiation prior to transplantation.
CDRH Definition: Patient required additional radiation therapy.

NCIt Definition: The measures applied for the restoration a person to life and/or consciousness. The act of resuscitation includes such components as artificial respiration and cardiac massage.
CDRH Definition: Patient required resuscitation.

NCIt Definition: Patient required programming changes to be made to an implantable or other programmable device.
CDRH Definition: Patient required programming changes to be made to an implantable or other programmable device.

NCIt Definition: Patient required non-surgical treatment under anesthesia.
CDRH Definition: Patient required non-surgical treatment under anaesthesia.

NCIt Preferred Term: Insufficient Information to Classify Health Impact
NCIt Definition: Not enough information available to classify the health impact.
CDRH Definition: It is not clear whether any health impact occurred, or health impact appears to have occurred, but there is not yet enough information available to classify the health impact.

NCIt Definition: Complication occurring in the patient that had not previously been identified or expected for this device.
CDRH Definition: Complication occurring in the patient that had not previously been identified or expected for this device.

NCIt Preferred Term: Adverse Event with No Consequence or Impact
NCIt Definition: No apparent harm occurred in relation to the adverse event.
CDRH Definition: No apparent harm occurred in relation to the adverse event.

NCIt Definition: The adverse event occurred during or immediately prior to a clinical procedure, but the problem was identified and corrected before harm could be caused.
CDRH Definition: The adverse event occurred during or immediately prior to a clinical procedure, but the problem was identified and corrected before harm could be caused. E.g.1. an IVD gave a false reading but it was recognized as incorrect before treatment decisions were made and without any clinically significant delay to diagnosis;E.g.2. a surgical device malfunctioned during pre-use checks and the malfunction was corrected or an alternative device was available without any clinically significant delay to the procedure.

NCIt Definition: An adverse event occurred while a device was being used in a non-clinical setting and/or procedure and could not have any impact on a patient.
CDRH Definition: The adverse event occurred while the device was being used in a non-clinical setting and/or procedure and could not have any impact on a patient. E.g.1. an IVD gave a false reading when testing an External Quality Assessment (EQA) sample; E.g.2. a surgical device malfunctioned during cleaning and/or maintenance.

NCIt Definition: No patient involvement when the adverse event occurred.
CDRH Definition: No patient involvement when the adverse event occurred (for example happened during set-up or cleaning).

NCIt Preferred Term: Appropriate Health Impact Term/Code Not Available
NCIt Definition: There is no appropriate Health Impact term or code.
CDRH Definition: The Health Impact is not adequately described by any other term. Note: this code must not be used unless there is no other feasible code. The preferred term should be documented when submitting an adverse event report. This information will be used to determine if a new term should be added to the code table.

NCIt Preferred Term: Death Not Related to Adverse Event
NCIt Definition: A death has occurred, but it was confirmed that the event did not contribute to the death.
CDRH Preferred Term: Death not related to reported adverse event
CDRH Definition: A death has occurred, but it was confirmed that the event did not contribute to the death. Other terms may also be selected if it is possible to link the adverse event to other identifiable health impacts.

CDRH Definition: A long, thin, multistranded electrical wire designed to carry signals or power over a distance.
